latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A SKYLIGHT SPACE | @ROWDTLA

Once the historic LA Terminal Market, ROW DTLA is a compilation of impressive industrial buildings built a century ago and designed to support Los Angeles’ commercial spirit. Sprawled over 2 million sqft along the Southern Pacific Railroad, the LA Terminal Market played a critical role in the distribution of produce and goods throughout the region. Today, in the early morning hours, the local grocery distributors continue to meet at the Produce Market adjacent to ROW DTLA, where they have met since the early 1900s.

Let us help you access the inaccessible. | hello@skylightstudios.com
"The Renaissance Of Brick-And-Mortar Locations As Ad Space" - @forbes

"Buildings as branding, buildings to tell stories, buildings to make places. Skylight studios take storied and important buildings and reinvents their future quickly while the redevelopment process churns on in the background."

Skylight CEO @stephanienblake joined @rethinkrealestateforgood's Eve Picker to talk adaptive reuse and the importance of digital companies creating physical experiences to build community. Listen via link in bio.

Artist and self-proclaimed 'photograffeur' @JR works to expand the meaning and power of public art through his ambitious projects that give visibility to communities and individuals across the globe.

"Since Russia’s invasion began, dozens of Ukraine’s 7.5 million children have been killed and thousands of others have left in search of safety, writes Tara Law.

Among those thousands is 5-year-old Valeriia from Kryvyi Rih, President Volodymyr Zelensky’s hometown in central Ukraine.

A drone was used to capture the cover image, which features a 148-ft. photo of Valeriia held up by more than 100 people outside the National Operal in Lviv on March 14."

latestIgtvVideos.title: Skylight Steelworks – 2020 Site Tour (Hamilton, ON)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
In celebration of Skylight Steelworks' one year anniversary, we are excited to share newly expanded on-site filming locations and brand new virtual tools, including extensive aerial footage, drone videos and 360° photos produced by Drone Unit. 

Skylight Steelworks offers unprecedented film, photo, and experiential locations that invite a new class of creators to explore waterfront scenery, industrial foundations, office spaces, authentic machinery, and sprawling warehouses. Across a vast acreage, these diverse spaces can be transformed into virtually any setting and made flexible for producing content in the new normal.

Location: Skylight Steelworks – Hamilton, ON (Canada) 

Film: @droneunit667

A SKYLIGHT SPACE | THE PENN DISTRICT is a revitalized gathering place that embodies the rhythm of New York to its fullest extent. From commuters to entertainment-seekers, from locals to tourists—THE PENN DISTRICT has a captive audience for brand placements, strategic event productions, digital signage and more.

Both within THE PENN DISTRICT and surrounding it are best-in-class venues, productions, and major cultural events. By partnering throughout THE PENN DISTRICT, partners have the opportunity to align their brand voice around key moments in culture.

Learn more at hello@byskylight.com

Once defined by industry, Williamsburg’s shoreline has been transformed into a dynamic district built for how New Yorkers live today. Historic buildings reactivated, infrastructure redesigned for resilience, and public spaces opened to the East River, all part of a long-term vision for sustainable, community-first development.

This is urban transformation by design—and by intention.

📍Photography by Dan Levin
